Indonesian Foreign Ministry spokesman Arramatta Nasir dismissed the group's claim, telling reporters in Jakarta that "Indonesia is still a democratic system and a free press, so it would be difficult to hide evidence of human rights abuses".
The locals want more foreign governments to pay attention to the situation.
