Indonesia will hold a new presidential election in 2019, but the Papuans say they are unlikely to vote for Jokowi again.
"Jocovy is a well-intentioned man, but he is surrounded by people involved in the Paniai shooting", says Gobay, chairman of the tribal council.
He wants Jokiv to know that the people of Paniai, besides living in the shadow of a greedy army, are mired in poverty and have a poor education and health system.
Gobai says that the people of Paniai, like other Papuans, consider their vote for Jokovi a debt that he must pay.
