The seminar takes place less than two months after his death; the journalists discuss their shared trauma, their nightmares, their insomnia, their paranoia.
Although the Office of the Special Federal Prosecutor was established in 2010 to investigate journalist cases, so far, according to the Committee to Protect Journalists, only two cases have been investigated.
As with most of the thousands of drug-related and organized crime-related murders that occur every year, the killers of journalists rarely face justice.
Riodosa journalists insist they will report on the violence in Sinaloa, even though they are devastated, even though it is much more dangerous out there.
Without information about the killers, without justice, talking about security at meetings is of little use", says Ibarra.
