He decided to move to the position of director for the coordination of production, - said at the enterprise. - Andrei Ohlopkov has fully fulfilled the task set before him to ensure the launch minimum for the first launch at the Vostochny cosmodrome.
Mr. Ohlopkov moved to work in the CENKI in 2013, having served in the space forces, in particular on Baikonur, and in Plesetsk - at the "northern" cosmodrome, he held the post of first deputy commander in the rank of colonel.
In 2009, Andrey Ohlopkov became a criminal case.
The investigation accused him of bribery: allegedly from his filing, regional merchants received state orders for the withdrawal, but did not fulfill the obligations taken to clean up the separated parts of the rocket carriers in the Arkhangelsk region and the Komi Republic.
In 2012, a jury found him not guilty.
The responsibilities he was given at the CENKI for technological development extended to various projects, but the main one was the construction of a cosmodrome in the Far East.
Oleg Ostapenko, who was then head of the Federal Space Agency, told "Kommersant" that the situation in the East "was critical already in October 2013".
The fact is that a strategic error was made in the planning: the completion of construction and the first launch of the Soyuz-2.1 rocket were planned for the same time - the end of 2015.
To complete the launch before the end of the year, the construction was completed six months earlier and the deadline was moved from December to July 2015.
To speed up the process, the specialists of the CENKI began to conduct the parallel installation of technological equipment on unfinished objects.
The main supporter of this idea was Andrei Okhlopkov.
Despite the risks and the delay (the Soyuz was launched on April 28, 2016 instead of December 2015), the idea was justified, says a source at the spaceport: "Otherwise, we would not have launched any missions from the Eastern, but would have been engaged in construction".
Vice-Premier Dmitry Rogozin, who oversaw the creation of the cosmodrome, jokingly called Andrei Okhlopkov his "cosmic Susany", but it was he who almost always requested information about the progress of construction.
Mr. Ochlopkov remembered and straightforwardly: for example, in an interview with "Ъ" he proposed to deprive the Federal Agency for Special Construction (Specstroy) of the status of the sole executor in the East and directly work with subcontractors: "Why should we put all the eggs in one basket of Specstroy?"
This idea found support in the government.
Since 2017, TsENKI has assumed the duties of a general contractor to complete construction and installation work on the start-up and technical complex by the planned start-up in the fourth quarter.
According to "Ъ", the reason for the transition of Mr. Ohlopkov to a new place of work was the disagreement with the leadership of the CENKI regarding the methods of completing the construction of structures and complexes of the cosmodrome, as well as the methods of working with subcontracted organizations.
"It was decided that this would be the best for everyone", says one of the top managers involved in the construction of the East Building.
A government official, in turn, called the decision strange: "He was one of the best specialists, it will not be easy to find a suitable replacement".
According to "Ъ", this will not be necessary: the position of technical director of the cosmodrome will be abolished, and its functions will be distributed among the divisions of the CNE.
