In Ukraine, they offered to send Russians to prison for illegally crossing the border
The Ukrainian Verkhovna Rada has registered a draft law that could criminalise Russians for illegally crossing the Ukrainian border.
According to RT, a document registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian parliament implies a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens who try to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for repeated offence or act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased up to five years.
If the offender was caught at the border with the weapon, then the custody time for him will increase to eight years.
Earlier it was reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians trying to get into Russia outside the established checkpoints.
