In Russia, two new territories of advanced social and economic development will appear - "Abaza" and "Novotroytsk".
The relevant decrees of the Russian government will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the ROD in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are determined.
In the city, where 15 thousand people live, there will be a special legal regime for entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment to the city, and also create more than 600 new jobs.
The list of economic activities in which the TOR "Abaza" will operate a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, for example, include plantation, livestock, food, soft drinks and clothing.
The Government of the Republic has already signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise "Abakanskyi rudnik" LLC.
In January 2017, the regional authorities reported that Khakasia had fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of the TOR.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novorossiysk, a territory of advanced socio-economic development will also be created.
This will diversify the economy of the monograd, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise "Ural Steel" JSC, as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities, which will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs in the new TRP, includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicinal products and medical materials.
Noroick became the first of the monotonochors of the Orenburg region to receive the status of a TOR.
We will remind that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment and improve the life of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOR can be distinguished the following: income tax in the amount of not more than 5% during the first five years, and not less than 10% during the next 5 years, social contributions in the amount of 7.6% for 10 years, use of the free customs zone regime, preferential regime of connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rates on rent.
